    "summary": "On H=L^2(R^d), define |p| and a radial multiplier ζ(x)=2(4-d)/|x|^2. For a simple trace expression Tr(|p| ζ |p|^{-1} ζ), insert Fourier and position resolutions to obtain a mixed kernel f(k,q,x,y). Evaluate f on the diagonal (q=k, x=y=x0) at d=6, then apply \"inverse then divide by 3\" to get an integer output.\n",
